    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-04T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-04T06:00:00-05:00" n="760"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d760">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760m.61/80: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_SLA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-04T14:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 4, 1939—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 4—9:18 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>673. The press reports the arrival of the Lithuanian Minister for Foreign Affairs
                    yesterday and a 2–hour conversation in the evening with <persName
                        corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> at which <persName corresp="#p_SIV1"
                        >Stalin</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_PVP1">Potemkin</persName>, the
                    Soviet Chargé d’Affaires in Kaunas, and the Lithuanian Minister in Moscow were
                    present. No indication of the subjects under discussion is given.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Kaunas.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
